5000|$|For a <b>refresh</b> <b>rate</b> of 600 Hz to be {{displayed}} correctly, an LCD {{would require a}} response time of approximately 1.667 (...) milliseconds GtG (grey-to-grey). In addition to {{the technical aspects of}} achieving such a high <b>refresh</b> <b>rate,</b> there are limits to the capability of the human eye. However, improving the response time of LCD pixels would improve the image quality for <b>refresh</b> <b>rates</b> that are on the fringe of what the human eye is capable of processing.|$|R
